statusTexts.name: statusTexts
statusTexts.long_desc:
The list of codes is complete according to the
{@link http://www.iana.org/assignments/http-status-codes/ Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) Status Code Registry}
(last updated 2016-03-01).

Unless otherwise noted, the status code is defined in RFC2616.

value.value: Reserved for WebDAV advanced collections expired proposal

__construct.name: __construct
exceptions: When the HTTP status code is not valid

__toString.name: __toString
__toString.short_desc: Returns the Response as an HTTP string.
__toString.long_desc:
The string representation of the Response is the same as the
one that will be sent to the client only if the prepare() method
has been called before.
__toString.hint_desc: The Response as an HTTP string

prepare.name: prepare
prepare.short_desc: Prepares the Response before it is sent to the client.
prepare.long_desc:
This method tweaks the Response to ensure that it is
compliant with RFC 2616. Most of the changes are based on
the Request that is "associated" with this Response.

sendContent.name: sendContent
sendContent.short_desc: Sends content for the current web response.

setContent.name: setContent
setContent.long_desc: Valid types are strings, numbers, null, and objects that implement a __toString() method.

content.name: content
content.short_desc: Content that can be cast to string

setProtocolVersion.name: setProtocolVersion
setProtocolVersion.short_desc: Sets the HTTP protocol version (1.0 or 1.1).

setStatusCode.name: setStatusCode
setStatusCode.long_desc:
If the status text is null it will be automatically populated for the known
status codes and left empty otherwise.
exceptions: When the HTTP status code is not valid

getStatusCode.name: getStatusCode
getStatusCode.short_desc: Retrieves the status code for the current web response.

isCacheable.name: isCacheable
isCacheable.short_desc: Returns true if the response may safely be kept in a shared (surrogate) cache.
isCacheable.long_desc:
Responses marked "private" with an explicit Cache-Control directive are
considered uncacheable.

Responses with neither a freshness lifetime (Expires, max-age) nor cache
validator (Last-Modified, ETag) are considered uncacheable because there is
no way to tell when or how to remove them from the cache.

Note that RFC 7231 and RFC 7234 possibly allow for a more permissive implementation,
for example "status codes that are defined as cacheable by default [...]
can be reused by a cache with heuristic expiration unless otherwise indicated"
(https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.1)

isFresh.name: isFresh
isFresh.short_desc: Returns true if the response is "fresh".
isFresh.long_desc:
Fresh responses may be served from cache without any interaction with the
origin. A response is considered fresh when it includes a Cache-Control/max-age
indicator or Expires header and the calculated age is less than the freshness lifetime.

isValidateable.name: isValidateable
isValidateable.short_desc:
Returns true if the response includes headers that can be used to validate
the response with the origin server using a conditional GET request.

setPrivate.name: setPrivate
setPrivate.long_desc: It makes the response ineligible for serving other clients.

setPublic.name: setPublic
setPublic.long_desc: It makes the response eligible for serving other clients.

isImmutable.name: isImmutable
isImmutable.short_desc: Returns true if the response is marked as "immutable".

mustRevalidate.name: mustRevalidate
mustRevalidate.short_desc: Returns true if the response must be revalidated by caches.
mustRevalidate.long_desc:
This method indicates that the response must not be served stale by a
cache in any circumstance without first revalidating with the origin.
When present, the TTL of the response should not be overridden to be
greater than the value provided by the origin.

getDate.name: getDate
getDate.short_desc: Returns the Date header as a DateTime instance.
exceptions: When the header is not parseable

getAge.name: getAge
getAge.short_desc: Returns the age of the response in seconds.

expire.name: expire
expire.short_desc: Marks the response stale by setting the Age header to be equal to the maximum age of the response.

getExpires.name: getExpires
getExpires.short_desc: Returns the value of the Expires header as a DateTime instance.

setExpires.name: setExpires
setExpires.short_desc: Sets the Expires HTTP header with a DateTime instance.
setExpires.long_desc: Passing null as value will remove the header.

getMaxAge.name: getMaxAge
getMaxAge.short_desc:
Returns the number of seconds after the time specified in the response's Date
header when the response should no longer be considered fresh.
getMaxAge.long_desc:
First, it checks for a s-maxage directive, then a max-age directive, and then it falls
back on an expires header. It returns null when no maximum age can be established.

setMaxAge.name: setMaxAge
setMaxAge.short_desc: Sets the number of seconds after which the response should no longer be considered fresh.
setMaxAge.long_desc: This methods sets the Cache-Control max-age directive.

setSharedMaxAge.name: setSharedMaxAge
setSharedMaxAge.short_desc: Sets the number of seconds after which the response should no longer be considered fresh by shared caches.
setSharedMaxAge.long_desc: This methods sets the Cache-Control s-maxage directive.

getTtl.name: getTtl
getTtl.short_desc: Returns the response's time-to-live in seconds.
getTtl.long_desc:
It returns null when no freshness information is present in the response.

When the responses TTL is <= 0, the response may not be served from cache without first
revalidating with the origin.

setTtl.name: setTtl
setTtl.short_desc: Sets the response's time-to-live for shared caches in seconds.
setTtl.long_desc: This method adjusts the Cache-Control/s-maxage directive.

setClientTtl.name: setClientTtl
setClientTtl.short_desc: Sets the response's time-to-live for private/client caches in seconds.
setClientTtl.long_desc: This method adjusts the Cache-Control/max-age directive.

getLastModified.name: getLastModified
getLastModified.short_desc: Returns the Last-Modified HTTP header as a DateTime instance.
exceptions: When the HTTP header is not parseable

setLastModified.name: setLastModified
setLastModified.short_desc: Sets the Last-Modified HTTP header with a DateTime instance.
setLastModified.long_desc: Passing null as value will remove the header.

getEtag.name: getEtag
getEtag.short_desc: Returns the literal value of the ETag HTTP header.

etag.name: etag
etag.short_desc: The ETag unique identifier or null to remove the header

weak.name: weak
weak.short_desc: Whether you want a weak ETag or not

setCache.name: setCache
setCache.short_desc: Sets the response's cache headers (validation and/or expiration).
setCache.long_desc: Available options are: etag, last_modified, max_age, s_maxage, private, public and immutable.

setNotModified.name: setNotModified
setNotModified.short_desc: Modifies the response so that it conforms to the rules defined for a 304 status code.
setNotModified.long_desc:
This sets the status, removes the body, and discards any headers
that MUST NOT be included in 304 responses.

hasVary.name: hasVary
hasVary.short_desc: Returns true if the response includes a Vary header.

getVary.name: getVary
getVary.short_desc: Returns an array of header names given in the Vary header.

replace.name: replace
replace.short_desc: Whether to replace the actual value or not (true by default)

isNotModified.name: isNotModified
isNotModified.short_desc:
Determines if the Response validators (ETag, Last-Modified) match
a conditional value specified in the Request.
isNotModified.long_desc:
If the Response is not modified, it sets the status code to 304 and
removes the actual content by calling the setNotModified() method.
isNotModified.hint_desc: true if the Response validators match the Request, false otherwise

isServerError.name: isServerError
isServerError.short_desc: Was there a server side error?

isNotFound.name: isNotFound
isNotFound.short_desc: Is the response a not found error?

isRedirect.name: isRedirect
isRedirect.short_desc: Is the response a redirect of some form?

closeOutputBuffers.name: closeOutputBuffers
closeOutputBuffers.short_desc: Cleans or flushes output buffers up to target level.
closeOutputBuffers.long_desc: Resulting level can be greater than target level if a non-removable buffer has been encountered.

ensureIEOverSSLCompatibility.name: ensureIEOverSSLCompatibility
ensureIEOverSSLCompatibility.short_desc: Checks if we need to remove Cache-Control for SSL encrypted downloads when using IE < 9.
